22/10/2003
LJUBLJANA, Slovenia -- Bulgaria and Slovenia signed an agreement Tuesday (21 October) on avoiding double taxation. 
The accord was signed during a meeting of the joint commission for economic co-operation. 
Representatives discussed issues in the fields of trade, tourism, standardisation, transportation, agriculture and energy.
In other news, Bulgarian Foreign Minister Solomon Passy welcomed his Kuwaiti counterpart, Sheikh Sabah al-Ahmad al-Jabir al Sabah, to Sofia on Tuesday. 
It was the first such visit in 20 years and is aimed at boosting bilateral economic ties. 
(Trud, 24 Chassa - 22/10/03; BTA, STA, BNT - 21/10/03)
